@startuml tenant-provisioning
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam defaultFontName Segoe UI
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #4A90D9
    ActorBorderColor #4A90D9
    LifeLineBorderColor #4A90D9
    ParticipantBorderColor #4A90D9
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #EBF4FF
    BoxBorderColor #4A90D9
}

title Tenant Registration & Provisioning Flow

actor "New Admin" as Admin
participant "Web App" as Web
participant "API Server" as API
participant "Email Service" as Email
participant "Wolverine\n(Job Runner)" as Jobs
database "PostgreSQL\n(public schema)" as PubDB
database "PostgreSQL\n(tenant schema)" as TenantDB

Admin -> Web: Fill registration form\n(org name, email, password)
Web -> API: POST /auth/register
API -> PubDB: Save organization (status: PENDING)\nSave user (status: UNVERIFIED)
API -> Email: Send verification email
API --> Web: 202 Accepted\n"Check your email"

Admin -> Web: Click verification link\n(token in email)
Web -> API: POST /auth/verify-email?token=...
API -> PubDB: Mark user as VERIFIED\nMark org as PROVISIONING
API -> Jobs: Enqueue ProvisionTenantJob(orgId)
API --> Web: 200 OK → Redirect to workspace

note over Jobs: Async provisioning begins

Jobs -> PubDB: Generate schema name\n(tenant_{org_slug})
Jobs -> TenantDB: CREATE SCHEMA tenant_{slug}
Jobs -> TenantDB: Run EF Core migrations\n(create all base tables)
Jobs -> PubDB: Assign Admin role to user\nMark org as ACTIVE
Jobs -> Email: Send "Welcome to Axis" email

note over Admin, Web: User is already in the workspace\nUI polls for org.status = ACTIVE\nthen shows the dashboard

@enduml
